Únase a nosotros el 23 de septiembre, 5-7pm para una sesión virtual de información sobre DACA (Acción Diferida para los Llegados en la Infancia) Socios de Navigate, Unidos MN, y un abogado de inmigración estarán disponibles para responder a sus preguntas. Puede unirse por Zoom o mirar a través de una transmisión en vivo en nuestra página de Facebook.

Join us Sept. 23, 5-7pm for a virtual info session about DACA (Deferred Action for Childhood Arrivals). Partners from Navigate, Unidos MN and an immigration lawyer will be available to answer your questions. You can join by Zoom or watch the livestream on our Facebook page.

Free COVID testing sites

South Minneapolis Testing

The Minnesota Department of Health (MDH) will host a free COVID-19 testing event on August 25, 2020 from 11am-7pm at the McKnight Early Childhood Family Development Center (4225 3rd Ave S. Minneapolis, MN 55409). Please promote this opportunity to anyone you know who lives in the surrounding area. Flyers are available (attached to this email) in English, Hmong, Somali, and Spanish. Click the following links to register online in English, Hmong, Somali, and Spanish.

North Minneapolis Testing

The Minnesota Department of Health (MDH) will host a free COVID Testing Event on Friday, August 28, 2020 from 12pm–7pm at New Salem Missionary Baptist Church (2507 N. Bryant Ave Minneapolis, MN 55411). This will be a walk-up event, with a goal of testing 500 North Minneapolis residents. Please help us promote this free testing opportunity to North Minneapolis residents. Flyers are available in English, Somali, Spanish, Hmong (see attached). Registration is available online in English, Hmong, Spanish, and Somali, or by phone at 1-855-612-0677.

post_text:
Hello everybody!

A little late on pride month. However, this month has been the most important pride month in recent years. It’s reinforced for us that our freedom is tied to everyone’s freedom. This month and EVERY month we stand in solidarity with Black Lives Matter. In the Stonewall riots, black and brown queer bodies were at the forefront in fighting for freedom of the LGBTQIA community. To recognize, name that, and power the voices of BIPOC people is our responsibility now and forever.

So happy pride to the most authentic pride we’ve had in a long time. Let’s fight for justice and liberation!

Love • Uplift • Heal • Fight • Justice • Self-Care

Also always ask for pronouns. 😉

Yours truly,
- A Queer POC at Hiawatha Academies

Minnesota Department of Education Survey
As they plan for SY20-21, the MN Department of Education wants to hear about families’ experiences with distance learning.

Please note: Hiawatha Academies WILL NOT have access to any feedback you share with the Department of Education. If you have any ideas or recommendations that you want us to see and respond to, please share those directly with a Hiawatha staff member.

----------------
Encuesta del Departamento de Educación de Minnesota
Mientras planean para SY20-21, el Departamento de Educación de MN quiere escuchar acerca de las experiencias de las familias con el aprendizaje a distancing.

Tenga en cuenta: Las Academias Hiawatha NO tendrán acceso a ningún comentario que comparta con el Departamento de Educación.Si tiene alguna idea o recomendación que desea que veamos y respondamos, compártala directamente con un miembro del personal de Hiawatha.

shared_text:
Unidos MN
June 11 at 4:27 PM ·

*** APLIQUEN HOY ***
www.unidos-mn.org/poderfellows

Querida comunidad,

En medio del cambio social, se nos recuerda que las victorias que estamos viendo ahora son el fruto de muchos años, sudor y lágrimas de jóvenes negros, indígenas, indocumentados o queer que se han organizado implacablemente por la justicia.

Como organización comunitaria fundada por jóvenes, comprendemos la urgencia de apoyar y fomentar el desarrollo del liderazgo de los adultos jóvenes, es por eso que estamos entusiasmados de abrir nuestra convocatoria de solicitudes para Poder Fellows 2020.

Esto es un programa de liderazgo en nuestra organización, remunerado, para adultos jóvenes. 19-25 que viven en el área metropolitana y Worthington. Estamos formando un equipo de líderes que están listos para asumir su poder y liderar nuestra comunidad. ¿Sabías que naciste para liderar este momento?

Visite unidos-mn.org/poderfellows para aplicar. Último día para solicitudes: viernes 26 de junio

Para obtener más información, comuníquese con Estefania Navarro a estefania@unidos-mn.org

post_text:
Si no puede pagar el alquiler o los servicios públicos este mes porque ha perdido ingresos debido a COVID-19, puede calificar para la Asistencia de Alquiler de Emergencia del Condado de Hennepin para hogares de bajos ingresos. Se dará prioridad a los hogares con ingresos extremadamente bajos que no sean elegibles para el seguro de desempleo. Aprenda más y solicite: www.hennepin.us/rent-help
*Las solicitudes están disponibles en varios idiomas.
----
If you can’t afford rent or utilities this month because you’ve lost income due to COVID-19, you may qualify for Hennepin County Government Emergency Rental Assistance for low-income households. Priority will be given to extremely low-income households who are not eligible for Unemployment insurance. Learn more and apply: www.hennepin.us/rent-help *Applications are available in multiple languages.

URGENT: EXECUTIVE ORDER

Minneapolis/St.Paul curfew is for all public places, including streets, stretching from 8 p.m. to 6 a.m, MAY 29. It’s in effect beginning Friday night, and will happen again at 8 p.m. on Saturday night.

Violating this order will result in a misdemeanor, subject to a $1,000 fine or imprisonment for up to 90 days.

---------------
URGENTE: ORDEN EJECUTIVA

Una toque de queda esta en efecto para Minneapolis y St. Paul para todos los lugares públicos, incluyendo las calles, empezando HOY a las 8pm hasta las 6am 29 DE MAYO. También está en efecto para mañana, Sábado, empezando a las 8pm.

Violando esta toque de queda resultará en un delito menor, una multa de $1,000, o encarcelamiento por hasta 90 días.

Read more at: https://hiawathaacademies.org/announcements/

post_text:
Our school responsibility is to hold close our students, families and staff as they grieve the impact of George Floyd’s death. Moving forward, we have a responsibility to look inward, and critically examine the policies and practices that perpetuate systemic racism within our network.

Nuestra responsabilidad de escuela es mantener cercanos a nuestros estudiantes, familias y personal mientras ellos están afligidos por el impacto de la muerte de George Floyd. En el futuro, tenemos una responsabilidad de ser introspectivos, y analizar críticamente las políticas y prácticas que perpetúan el racismo sistémico dentro de nuestra red.

post_text:
Welcome to Wellness Wednesdays at Hiawatha Academies. Every Wednesday, we will post video messages from our School Nurse, School Psychologist, and other guests to share knowledge and tips with our community for staying healthy and promoting wellbeing during this strange and difficult time. Videos will be posted in English, Spanish and Somali. We hope you'll join us:) Please post questions or suggested topics and we will address them in future videos.

Note: Vidoes will be posted in Somali too starting next week. Thank you for understanding!

Where do we even BEGIN! Thank you, thank you, thank you to our beloved teachers, staff and educators for supporting our scholars and families. Especially now, when times are tough, you have risen to the moment and redefined what teaching means. REDEFINED what it means to commit.

We are and eternally grateful for your time, your energy, your love and your dedication to your craft. We applaud you, we celebrate you, we commend you. Thank a teacher today!

#GiveAtHome starts today!

Our scholars are still growing and still learning!

To date we have distributed 770 laptop devices to 65% of our families who needed it. But our work isn’t over yet. 12% of our families still do not have access to the basic right of access to the internet! We are working on solutions and need your help to reach the finish line, the final push! Thank you 🙏

To donate, go to https://www.givemn.org/story/Hiawathacovid-19relief

post_text:
Ramadan Mubarak - Happy Ramadan, wishing you the best.
•
Today evening marks the beginning of Ramadan, the holiest month in the Islamic calendar during which many Muslims fast from sunrise to sunset. Ramadan is a month filled with gatherings of family, friends and community, both for daily iftar meals to break the fast at sunset and for prayer in mosques.

This year many of these community rituals will not be possible due to the COVID-19 crisis and the restrictions on gatherings. For our families and community members celebrating Ramadan in these unprecedented times, we want to send our love and warmest wishes

Today the City of Minneapolis launched the Minneapolis Emergency Housing Fund to help renters who have lost income due to COVID-19. Immigration status is NOT a barrier; all who need help should apply. Applications will be accepted through noon Monday, April 27.

Funds are limited, so we encourage you to apply right away. To apply visit: http://www.minneapolismn.gov/coronavirus/gap-funding or call the Tenant Resource Center (612-302-3129) and leave a voicemail.
-------------

Hoy la Ciudad de Minneapolis inició el Fondo de Emergencia de Minneapolis para ayudar a inquilinos quienes han perdido ingresos debido al COVID-19. El estatus de inmigración NO es una barrera; todos los que necesiten ayuda deberían aplicar. Las aplicaciones serán aceptadas hasta el mediodía del lunes 27 de Abril.

Los fondos son limitados, así que los alentamos a aplicar inmediatamente.
Para aplicar visite: http://www.minneapolismn.gov/coronavirus/gap-funding o llame al Tenant Resource Center (Centro de Recursos de Inquilinos, 612-302-3129) y deje un mensaje de voz.

shared_text:
Hiawatha College Prep - Kingfield
February 7 at 9:48 PM ·

Last week, we had our Career and College Panel to open the mind of students to learn more information about careers they have interest in and to give them insight on college. The event was a success!!! We want to thank all the volunteers who came and participated on the panel.

Community partners, HaoPay Lee Violence Free Minnesota , Representative Hodan Hassan Minnesota State Representative for 62A, and Yee Kue MANYC Technology Solutions.

College students, Yamileth Carachure Flores, Arianna Antone-Ramirez, Houa Thao Daniela Fragale Augsburg University and Pasuaha Yang University of St. Thomas for being transparent on how it is navigating college as students of color and sharing tips to set up students for success.

To our sister school Hiawatha Collegiate High School , we appreciate you sending students over to share their perspectives on what it takes to be high school ready. #onehiawatha

Last but not least, much gratitude to Get Ready Program for supporting us in putting this event together.

shared_text:
Reading Partners Twin Cities
January 23 at 5:39 PM ·

Today's #ThankATutor comes from Hallie at Hiawatha Academies Morris Park:

"This is Pam's second year tutoring with Reading Partners. Pam is amazingly flexible and energetic with the two students she tutors, a fourth grader AND a second grader. Her two students have very different personalities and learning styles, and Pam adapts very well. Pam also stepped up recently to help her fourth grade student, who is more quiet, and learns best when there is trust and consistency. When this student's other tutor, a college student, left after last semester, Pam started working with this student twice a week. This is so incredibly helpful because this student and Pam have built a trusting relationship. Instead of being anxious around a new person and rebuilding trust, this student can focus on learning. Thank you so much for setting this student up for success, Pam!"

Thanks so much for your energy, Pam! If you'd like to sign up to tutor, sign up at https://readingpartners.org/volunteer-twin-cities/#signup.

shared_text:
Reading Partners Twin Cities
January 21 at 11:51 PM ·

Today's #TutorTip comes from Hallie at Hiawatha Academies:

"Make sure to review which letters in the alphabet are consonants and which letters are vowels before starting a lesson that uses these terms! Many students are familiar with the concept that these letters are different, but many not remember the specific terms "consonant" and "vowel". Making sure the student is familiar with these terms before you start a lesson (especially if the lesson is about long vs. short vowel sounds) is extremely helpful and avoids confusion later! "

post_text:
Andrena Murphy is our second grade teacher at Hiawatha Leadership Academy - Northrop campus. Her instructional practice are based on the power of phonics; teaching our kids to decode language.
•
Phonics: a method of teaching people to read by correlating sounds with letters or groups of letters in an alphabetic writing system.
•
Teaching our kids to decode language is putting power into their hands to comprehend the world and initiate a unique structural learning at a young age.
•
•
•
#hiawathaleadsmn #school #education #phonics #humansofhoawatha
